text: RT @SenBooker Farmworkers & others who come into close contact with dangerous pesticides should at the very least have a basic level of protection—such as a right to safety information about the chemicals they're exposed to & an agreed-upon minimum age for handling dangerous pesticides.
RT @SenBooker Unfortunately, the Trump Administration is now proposing to weaken these common-sense protections—safeguards that have been 10 years in the making.
RT @SenBooker We know that certain pesticides can increase the risk of cancer and can negatively impact brain development in children—it is critical that we have adequate protections.

RT @SenBooker I’ve joined my colleagues @TomUdall @SenKamalaHarris & @SenBlumenthal pushing a compromise amendment to preserve these protections for agricultural workers & children, and allow a full reauthorization of the Pesticide Registration Enhancement Act #PRIA: https://www.scribd.com/document/372066291/Udall-Booker-Harris-Blumenthal-Offer-Compromise-to-Pesticide-Registration-Reauthorization-Stalemate
